parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rollaway Accident due to Lack of Safety Feature
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of a safety feature to prevent rollaway accidents when the vehicle is at full stop and the engine is turned off can cause the vehicle to roll, potentially leading to accidents or damage to the vehicle or surrounding property.
symptoms: The vehicle starts rolling after the engine is turned off
even when the transmission is in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature cracking of interior trim can lead to cosmetic damage and potentially affect the overall durability of the vehicle's interior components.
symptoms: Cracking of the trim around the front center A/C vent
cracking of the area around the cup holder.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle self-starting while unattended can lead to safety risks, such as carbon monoxide poisoning or accidents, and can also cause unnecessary fuel consumption.
symptoms: The vehicle starts running while unattended
with the engine running and dash lights on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An error in the VIN information can lead to issues with vehicle registration, insurance, and warranty claims.
symptoms: The VIN information displays an incorrect year of manufacture.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the Yokohama tire sidewall can lead to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The tire sidewall explodes or spits
a crack or split appears on the tire sidewall
the tire needs to be replaced due to manufacturing defect.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal to engage can cause the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle continues to accelerate despite repeated compression of the brakes
the brakes fail to slow or stop the vehicle
the driver has to pump the brake pedal to stop the vehicle.
